{
  "texts": [
    "Clade I was highly fatal and limited to Central Africa.",
    "In 2024, the new variant of clade I, clade Ib, is responsible for the MPOX pandemic.",
    "Some genes are absent or shortened in one or two clades, causing small gene content discrepancies.",
    "According to a recent study, Clade II contains three shorter genes (D4L, B14L, and B15L) and four missing genes (D14L, D15L, D16L, and D17L).",
    "The VACV-Cop E5R homologue is solely lacking in Clade I, and 3 of the genes (VACV-Cop A47L & B11R homologues and K1R) are truncated (Alakunle et al., 2024)."
  ]
}